\begin_layout Section*
Discussion
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
as expected from Copenhagen: OECD (2020) also provide an interesting point,
 that while big cities may suffer from a higher risk of fast spread of a
 disease like COVID-19 because of high population density, a greater potential
 for working from home can provide a source of resilience to the economic
 downturn following the COVID-19 crisis (OECD, 2020).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
sammenlign vores tal med disse: https://voxeu.org/article/potential-remote-workin
g-across-different-places?fbclid=IwAR2zo04l-Hdlz9Tn2fCRCs4itnG7rI4_SwjenBl4XK5nW
Ui2Y35yzCdQmmo
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Another interesting insight of remote job postings would be to identify
 which job functions are especially becoming more remote.
 See Højbjerre, Brauer & Schultz.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Discussion: If jobindex had a filter for “Fjernarbejde”, we could evaluate
 on this.
 By scraping the text in the job posting (however a problem with the old
 job postings, because the links are not working).
 Why do we want to KNOW this forecasting/prediction? What is the demand
 for people working remotely.
 brug til at lave en filter i jobindex
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
- Increasing demand/push: Arbejdsgiver organisation: https://www.danskindustri.dk/
vi-radgiver-dig-ny/personale/personalejura/vilkar-under-ansattelsen/personalepol
itik/hjemmearbejde/ + Virksomhedspanelet ang.
 hjemmearbejde and Political push: https://politiken.dk/oekonomi/art7882631/Vi-sk
al-igen-til-at-arbejde-hjemme
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
furhter research: explore different job functions.
 maybe mostly highly educated will work from home? this is what they find
 in https://www.dallasfed.org/-/media/documents/research/papers/2020/wp2017.pdf.
 and OECD (2020): the potential of remote work increases with the overall
 skill level of the population.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
–> Assessing remote working potential through a classification of occupations
 To assess regional differences in remote working potential, our study exploits
 the diversity of tasks performed in different types of occupations and
 the geographical distribution of those occupations.
 The assessment of remote working potential across regions consists of two
 steps.
 https://voxeu.org/article/potential-remote-working-across-different-places?fbcli
d=IwAR2zo04l-Hdlz9Tn2fCRCs4itnG7rI4_SwjenBl4XK5nWUi2Y35yzCdQmmo
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
....
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
HBS: Based on the company name, data is then linked to the Central Business
 register, where additional information is extracted about the size, industry
 and geographical location of the company.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Section*
Conclusion
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Even though it seems that remote work will expand in the future, not all
 jobs can be done remotely, and the potential for remote work therefore
 higly depends on the composition of the labour market including skill levels
\end_layout

